snippet.title: Dreama Collins
snippet.description:
From about 2014 - 2016 I was in a narcissistic relationship, only I didn't know it until near the end. This along with other abusive situations throughout my life (including having a narcissistic mother) led up to me trying to take my life on May 31, 2016. I should have died that day. I didn't. By the grace of God I was saved because those who knew me knew that post I made on Facebook was "off" and 13 folks called the police. Because of them & because God still had a purpose for my life, I am still here. Perhaps, it's to share my story and knowledge of narcissism and how to overcome it's abusive affects. All you have to do is take a baby step each day, that's all and eventually you WILL get to a good place again. I've written of my experiences in a book that can be purchased on Amazon. It's my prayer that you find your joy again, & if my experience helps, then it was worth it; even if it helps just one person.
https://www.amazon.com/dp/1698238916/ref=cm_sw_r_tw_dp_1A0JKZK0Z1V1A2549KGK
